 of Health</strong></a> – June 1, 2022. Presented by Leslie DeRosset and Nakenge Robertson. </p><p><a href="../../trainings/ATMCH-February-2022-Webinar.php"><strong>Introduction to Literature Reviews</strong></a> – February 3, 2022. Presented by W. Oscar Fleming, DrPH, Lan Le, MPA, John Richards, MA, and Keisha Watson, PhD.</p><p><a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="../../trainings/ATMCH-November-2020-Webinar.php"><strong>Achieving Real Engagement in the Virtual Classroom</strong></a> – November 5, 2020. Presented by <a href="https://www.karinrex.com/#/" target="_blank">Karin Rex</a>, MA, COTP (Certified Online Professional Facilitator). </p><p><a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Archived Webinar (opens in a new tab)" href="../../trainings/ATMCH-June-2020-Webinar.php"><strong>First Things First: An MCH Reset Retreat to Determine What Matters Now</strong></a> – June 22, 2020. Presented by Janine Hill, PhD(c), MPH, ACC – President, <a href="https://soar-strategies.com/" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Soar Strategies, Inc.  (opens in a new tab)">Soar Strategies, Inc. </a>&amp; Kris Risley, DrPH, CPCC – Managing Director, Workforce, <a href="https://www.debeaumont.org/" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="de Beaumont Foundation (opens in a new tab)">de Beaumont Foundation</a>.</p><p><strong><a href="../../trainings/ATMCH-March-2020-Webinar.php">Advancing MCH Graduate Training via Mobile Technology</a></strong> – March 2, 2020. Presented by Renee Davis, MD, MPH – MCH Program Coordinator/Research Associate, Drexel Dornsife School of Public Health. This project earned an ATMCH Innovative Teaching Award. To learn more &amp; access additional resources, click <a href="innovative-teaching-awards/advancing-mch-professional-engagement-via-mobile-technology.php" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="HERE (opens in a new tab)">HERE</a>.</p><p><strong><a href="../../trainings/ATMCH-November-2019-Webinar.php">Strategies for Developing Engaging Online Learning</a></